# Excel Reporter Safety Rules

- Keep logic/layout separation:
  - Business and scoring logic in crawler/pipeline/rules.
  - Workbook I/O, formatting, TOC, and view-state logic in reporter modules.
- Treat workbook integrity as highest priority for client-facing exports.
- Preserve ghost pane + freeze pane guardrails when changing sheet view state.
- Preserve nuclear view-state guardrails for small non-core sheets.
- Keep string sanitisation and formula-injection protections active on all written values.
- Keep TOC names, sheet names, and internal hyperlinks consistent.
- Keep Content Optimisation Hub action literals and conditional formatting aligned (`Needs Copy` red path).
